        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(web_fetch): strip whitespace from URLs to prevent new URL() parse errors",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nLLMs occasionally generate `web_fetch` URLs with accidental spaces (e.g. `\"https:// docs.example.com/page\"`) which cause `new URL()` to throw `Invalid URL: must be http or https`. This fix strips all whitespace from the URL before parsing, so such URLs are accepted and fetched correctly.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #91651\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** `web_fetch` tool rejects URLs with internal whitespace that LLMs may generate (e.g. space after `https://`).\n- **Real environment tested:** macOS, Node v22.22.3, latest upstream/main\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/tools/web-fetch.cf-markdown.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix (copied live output):**\n\n```\n ✓ web_fetch Cloudflare Markdown for Agents > sends Accept header preferring text/markdown\n ✓ web_fetch Cloudflare Markdown for Agents > uses cf-markdown extractor\n ✓ web_fetch Cloudflare Markdown for Agents > falls back to readability\n ✓ web_fetch Cloudflare Markdown for Agents > bypasses Firecrawl\n ✓ web_fetch Cloudflare Markdown for Agents > logs x-markdown-tokens\n ✓ web_fetch Cloudflare Markdown for Agents > converts markdown to text\n ✓ web_fetch Cloudflare Markdown for Agents > does not log x-markdown-tokens\n ✓ web_fetch Cloudflare Markdown for Agents > strips whitespace from URLs with internal spaces (#91651)\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  8 passed (8)\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** URLs with embedded spaces like `\"https:// docs.example.com/page\"` are cleaned to `\"https://docs.example.com/page\"` before `new URL()` parsing and before the HTTP fetch.\n- **What was not tested:** Live HTTP fetch with space-containing URLs (mock test verifies the fetch URL is cleaned correctly).\n- **Proof limitations or environment constraints:** None — the fix is a deterministic string operation.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n**Which commands did you run?**\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/tools/web-fetch.cf-markdown.test.ts\n# 8 passed (1 test file, including 1 new regression test)\n```\n\n**What regression coverage was added or updated?**\nAdded `\"strips whitespace from URLs with internal spaces\"` — fetches a URL with spaces, verifies the fetch call uses the cleaned URL.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n**Did user-visible behavior change?** Yes — URLs with spaces now succeed instead of throwing errors.\n**Did config, environment, or migration behavior change?** No\n**Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change?** No\n**What is the highest-risk area?** Could cause fetches to unexpected URLs if space removal creates a different valid URL. Mitigation: protocol check (http/https) and SSRF guard remain in place.\n**How is that risk mitigated?** URL is still validated after cleaning.\n\n## Current review state\n\n**What is the next action?** Maintainer review.\n**What is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?** None.\n\n---\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com>\n",
